ivity is.</p>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Supporting tools and guides","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>Click the links to discover more about our supporting tools and guides</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://theodi.org/article/anonymising-data-in-times-of-crisis/\" target=\"_blank\">Anonymising data in times of crisis – The ODI</a></li><li><a href=\"https://theodi.org/article/anonymisation-and-synthetic-data-towards-trustworthy-data/\" target=\"_blank\">Anonymisation and synthetic data: towards trustworthy data – The ODI</a></li><li><a href=\"https://odileeds.org/blog/2019-02-01-anonimisation-and-re-identification\" target=\"_blank\">Anonymisation and re-identification - ODI Leeds</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/theodi/synthetic-data-tutorial\" target=\"_blank\">A hands-on tutorial showing how to use Python to do anonymisation with synthetic data - The ODI</a></li></ul>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]}]},{"module":{"title":"Anonymising Data","aim":"<p>The aim of this module is to equip learners with the knowledge and skills necessary to effectively manage and mitigate risks associated with handling and sharing personal data. Through practical examples and hands-on exercises, participants will learn to establish lawful and ethical bases for data projects, set clear objectives, assess risks, apply anonymisation techniques, and implement processes for monitoring and responding to existing and new risks.</p>","learningOutcomes":[{"outcome":"Demonstrate an understanding of the ethical and legal considerations surrounding the handling and sharing of personal data."},{"outcome":"Identify appropriate lawful bases for anonymising data."},{"outcome":"Develop clear objectives for the anonymising of data that balance maximising utility with minimising risk."},{"outcome":"Assess the potential risks associated with handling and sharing personal data, including the risk o