 real world data used to test accuracy. Additionally, the dataset can be created under controlled conditions, minimising a number of biases and speeding up collection.</p>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Diagnosing the NHS: SynÆ","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>NHS England recognises that data is useful. Summary data about A&amp;E departments of UK hospitals are big news. Waiting times data is <a href=\"https://www.kingsfund.org.uk/projects/urgent-emergency-care/urgent-and-emergency-care-mythbusters\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">analysed</a> and fills front pages, the TV, and the radio. Things get political very quickly.</p><div class=\"callout\"><p>But an average waiting time doesn't tell us much about what's really happening.</p></div><p>Who needed care? At what time? For what problem? And what happened as a result?</p><p>Detailed A&amp;E admissions data is far too sensitive to be made open. It is rightly afforded <a href=\"https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/lawful-basis-for-processing/special-category-data/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">special category status within both the GDPR and The Data Protection Act 2018</a>.</p><p>Synthetic data provides a potential method through which statistically accurate data can be shared.</p><div class=\"callout\"><p>You can read more about the work of ODI Leeds and NHS England on creating synthetic A&amp;E data <a href=\"https://open-innovations.org/events/synae/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> including detail on the <a href=\"https://open-innovations.org/blog/2019-01-24-exploring-methods-for-creating-synthetic-a-e-data\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">methodology</a>.</p></div>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Do data protection regulations apply to anonymised or synthetic data?","type":"Question"},"components":[{"properties":{"instruction":"Choose one option then select Submit.","items":[{"text":"Yes","shouldBeSelected":false},{"text":"No","shouldBeSelected":true}],"feedback":{"correct":"<p><strong>That's right!</p></strong></p><p>Once the data is anonymised, data protection regulations no longer apply and data can be shared with others safely, even outside the geographical boundaries that may be imposed by data protection regulations.</p><p>However, this does not mean that the retention, use and sharing (or not sharing) of the data will be ethical, even if it is legal.</p>","incorrect":"<p><strong>Are you sure about that?</p></strong></p><p>Once the data is anonymised, data protection regulations no longer apply and data can be shared with others safely, even outside the geographical boundaries that may be imposed by data protection regulations.</p><p>However, this does not mean that the retention, use and sharing (or not sharing) of the data will be ethical, even if it is legal.</p>"}}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"STEP 5: Testing resilience","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<div class=\"heading-with-rule\"><p>Application to our example dataset</p></div><div class=\"padded-callout\"><p><strong>Remember the questions:</strong></p><ol><li>Is it possible to single out an individual?</li><li>Is it possible to link records relating to an individual using data already available to people?</li><li>Can information be inferred concerning an individual within the same dataset?</li></ol></div><p>Let’s apply these to the dataset:</p><div><div><table><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Example value</th><th>Q1</th><th>Q2</th><th>Q3</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Site Type</td><td>111,999</td><td>N</td><td>N</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Call date</td><td>2020-03-19</td><td>N</td><td>N</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Name</td><td>Joe Bloggs</td><td colspan=\"3\">REMOVED FROM DATA</td></tr><tr><td>Date of Birth</td><td>2005-06-03</td><td colspan=\"3\">REMOVED FROM