 with less risk of data protection infringement attached to it.</p><div class=\"callout\"><p><strong>Explore some case studies in synthetic data below</strong></p></div>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Synthetic data as training data for AI","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>One problem that can arise with AI systems is a lack of training data. For example, to train an AI to recognise defects from images of objects; it is first necessary to have images of defective objects. Rather than gather real world images, one potential is to create a synthetic dataset of objects with defects (ie. using CAD software).&nbsp;</p><p>This can then form 90% of the training data with real world data used to test accuracy. Additionally, the dataset can be created under controlled conditions, minimising a number of biases and speeding up collection.</p>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Diagnosing the NHS: SynÆ","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>NHS England recognises that data is useful. Summary data about A&amp;E departments of UK hospitals are big news. Waiting times data is <a href=\"https://www.kingsfund.org.uk/projects/urgent-emergency-care/urgent-and-emergency-care-mythbusters\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">analysed</a> and fills front pages, the TV, and the radio. Things get political very quickly.</p><div class=\"callout\"><p>But an average waiting time doesn't tell us much about what's really happening.</p></div><p>Who needed care? At what time? For what problem? And what happened as a result?</p><p>Detailed A&amp;E admissions data is far too sensitive to be made open. It is rightly afforded <a href=\"https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/guide-to-the-general-data-protection-regulation-gdpr/lawful-basis-for-processing/special-category-data/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">special category status within both the GDPR and The Data Protection Act 2018</a>.</p><p>Synthetic data provides a potential method through which statistically accurate data can be shared.</p><div class=\"callout\"><p>You can read more about the work of ODI Leeds and NHS England on creating synthetic A&amp;E data <a href=\"https://open-innovations.org/events/synae/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">here</a> including detail on the <a href=\"https://open-innovations.org/blog/2019-01-24-exploring-methods-for-creating-synthetic-a-e-data\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">methodology</a>.</p></div>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Do data protection regulations apply to anonymised or synthetic data?","type":"Question"},"components":[{"properties":{"instruction":"Choose one option then select Submit.","items":[{"text":"Yes","shouldBeSelected":false},{"text":"No","shouldBeSelected":true}],"feedback":{"correct":"<p><strong>That's right!</p></strong></p><p>Once the data is anonymised, data protection regulations no longer apply and data can be shared with others safely, even outside the geographical boundaries that may be imposed by data protection regulations.</p><p>However, this does not mean that the retention, use and sharing (or not sharing) of the data will be ethical, even if it is legal.</p>","incorrect":"<p><strong>Are you sure about that?</p></strong></p><p>Once the data is anonymised, data protection regulations no longer apply and data can be shared with others safely, even outside the geographical boundaries that may be imposed by data protection regulations.</p><p>However, this does not mean that the retention, use and sharing (or not sharing) of the data will be ethical, even if it is legal.</p>"}}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"STEP 5: Testing resilience","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<div class=\"heading-with-rule\"><p>Application to our example dataset</p></div><div class=\"padded-callout\"><p><strong>Remember the questions:</strong></p><ol><li>Is it possible to single out an individual?</li><li>Is it possible to link records relating to an individual using data already available to people?</li><li>Can information be inferred concerning an individual within the same dataset?</li></ol></div><p>Let’s apply these to the dataset:</p><div><div><table><thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Example value</th><th>Q1</th><th>Q2</th><th>Q3</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Site Type</td><td>111,999</td><td>N</td><td>N</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Call date</td><td>2020-03-19</td><td>N</td><td>N</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Name</td><td>Joe Bloggs</td><td colspan=\"3\">REMOVED FROM DATA</td></tr><tr><td>Date of Birth</td><td>2005-06-03</td><td colspan=\"3\">REMOVED FROM DATA</td></tr><tr><td>Age Band</td><td>0–18,19–69,70–120</td><td>N</td><td>N</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Town/City</td><td>Matlock</td><td>N</td><td>Potentially in some sparsely populated areas. Classifying as low risk.</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Postcode area</td><td>IG11</td><td>N</td><td>Potentially in some sparsely populated areas. Classifying as low risk.</td><td>N</td></tr><tr><td>Profession</td><td>Student, Counselor</td><td>N</td><td>N</td><td>N</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"STEP 6: Write a plan to mitigate risk","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>Rather than apply and plan to mitigate risk regarding our dataset, we applied this step to the whole of this guide. The guide was reviewed internally by senior members of the ODI team prior to publication to ensure our advice is both accurate and set in the right tone that provides the right balance between risk and utility.</p><p>Although the dataset was synthetic, some of the data points, e.g. postcodes, are realistic and could actually exist. This led us to still evaluating the risks and documenting our decision making in Step 1.</p>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"STEP 7: Publish the data, anonymisation details and risk assessment","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>This is hopefully exactly what this step by step example activity is.</p>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]},{"block":{"title":"Supporting tools and guides","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>Click the links to discover more about our supporting tools and guides</p><ul><li><a href=\"https://theodi.org/article/anonymising-data-in-times-of-crisis/\" target=\"_blank\">Anonymising data in times of crisis – The ODI</a></li><li><a href=\"https://theodi.org/article/anonymisation-and-synthetic-data-towards-trustworthy-data/\" target=\"_blank\">Anonymisation and synthetic data: towards trustworthy data – The ODI</a></li><li><a href=\"https://odileeds.org/blog/2019-02-01-anonimisation-and-re-identification\" target=\"_blank\">Anonymisation and re-identification - ODI Leeds</a></li><li><a href=\"https://github.com/theodi/synthetic-data-tutorial\" target=\"_blank\">A hands-on tutorial showing how to use Python to do anonymisation with synthetic data - The ODI</a></li></ul>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]}]},{"module":{"title":"Anonymising Data","aim":"<p>The aim of this module is to equip learners with the knowledge and skills necessary to effectively manage and mitigate risks associated with handling and sharing personal data. Through practical examples and hands-on exercises, participants will learn to establish lawful and ethical bases for data projects, set clear objectives, assess risks, apply anonymisation techniques, and implement processes for monitoring and responding to existing and new risks.</p>","learningOutcomes":[{"outcome":"Demonstrate an understanding of the ethical and legal considerations surrounding the handling and sharing of personal data."},{"outcome":"Identify appropriate lawful bases for anonymising data."},{"outcome":"Develop clear objectives for the anonymising of data that balance maximising utility with minimising risk."},{"outcome":"Assess the potential risks associated with handling and sharing personal data, including the risk of re-identification and potential harm."},{"outcome":"Apply anonymisation techniques effectively to mitigate the risks and protect individual privacy while maintaining the utility of the data."},{"outcome":"Evaluate the resilience of anonymisation techniques through testing and validation procedures."},{"outcome":"Plan the publication of data while considering anonymisation details and risk assessments to ensure compliance with data protection regulations and ethical principles."},{"outcome":"Implement processes for monitoring and responding to existing and emerging risks associated with data handling and sharing."}],"reflectiveQuestions":[{"question":"Consider the data you handle about people. Do you share it? Who do you share it with? How do you share it? And, most importantly, how do you protect it?"},{"question":"Is there any data that you don’t handle because of the risks associated with it? Are there any anonymisation techniques that could be applied to ensure that the value of the data can be realised whilst minimising the risk to individuals?"},{"question":"What could be done better at your organisation to ensure utility is maintained and privacy protected? Why?"}]},"content":[{"block":{"title":"Summary","type":"Title"},"components":[{"body":"<p>Data is anonymised to protect individuals' privacy. Anonymisation techniques are applied to personal or sensitive data, where there is a risk of re-identification and potential harm to an individual.</p><p>Anonymisation involves removing (suppression) or altering data (generalisation or randomisation) in a way that makes it impossible to identify specific individuals from the data. This process is crucial when sharing data for research, analysis, or other purposes, as it ensures that people's identities cannot be revealed.&nbsp;</p><p>Anonymised data helps prevent potential misuse, discrimination, or unauthorised access to sensitive information while still maintaining the utility of data and enabling organisations to use the data for valuable insights and decision-making.</p>","properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}},{"properties":{"instruction":"","items":[]}}]}]}]